# Modern Install Experience (Phase 24)

Read **[MODERN_INSTALL_EXPERIENCE.md](../../MODERN_INSTALL_EXPERIENCE.md)** before changes to install UX, tokens, platform detection, or escalations.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Installation Assistant, guided steps, knowledge-base UI | **Customer App** (`/app/install`) |
| Developer Settings (tokens, API keys, diagnostics) | **Customer App** (`/app/settings/developer`) |
| Token validation, heartbeat, domain/plan enforcement | **Install Engine** (`app/api/install/`) |

## Rules

1. Standard users never see install tokens — use `begin_modern_install` (no token in response)
2. Tokens only in Developer Settings after explicit rotation
3. Never log, email, or expose raw tokens in customer-facing UI
4. Platform detection must ask when uncertain — never guess silently
5. Domain ownership and plan limits enforced via `assert_license_capacity` server-side
6. Support escalations collect platform, domain, status, error summary only — no PII
7. Extend existing wizard/install engine — do not replace without migration plan
8. Knowledge-base guides in `lib/install/knowledge-base.ts` are the canonical install docs

> Customers should think: "That was incredibly simple."
